  "rationale": "WoodWave has no logo-wall or feature-grid, so social proof and value-props map onto editorial vocabulary. ACT 1 reuses/adapts the three seeded captured patterns: the inverse hero bookend (the ONLY accent + sanctioned display-title-over-media with overlap), a three-module value_props run adapted from features-split-feature into an open staggered stack (no boxed cards on cream), the gallery-mosaic-with-overflow with ghost-word + bleed + stagger + marginal-caption, and a stat/quote social-proof split on panel. ACT 2 expands the library with two novel off-grid sections the seed set lacks: an interlock statement float-wrapping the inset overlap-vase image, and a colossal 'Scales with you' collage with a heavy full-bleed image and staggered title. The page ends on a centered conversion stack. Exactly one inverse accent hero; every other section is primary/panel and accent-free; all actions are typographic arrow/slash links (no buttons), radius 0, no shadows, no gradients, captions in the margin."
}
